Getting started

##Setting up R packages

To start with, ggstatplot and tidyverse will be installed using library

packages = c('ggstatsplot', 'ggside', 'knitr',
             'tidyverse', 'broom', 'ggdist', 
             'gganimate', 'plotly',
             'crosstalk', 'DT')
for (p in packages){
  if(!require(p, character.only = T)){
    install.packages(p)
  }
}

Importing data

exam<-read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")
